    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Scruggs</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received September 28.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Venezuelan Government requests me to ask whether, in case <hi rend="italic"
                        >Portland</hi> cleared for Trinidad, but proceeded to Puerto Cabello direct,
                    our naval forces can interfere, as desired, in support of court’s decision and
                    strict neutrality.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scruggs.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
